                     <code code="44425-7" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="STORAGE AND HANDLING SECTION"/>
                     <title>Storage</title>
                     <text>
                        <paragraph>Store at 20° to 25°C (68° to 77°F) [see USP Controlled Room Temperature]. Exposing this product to very cold temperatures may result in crystallization of the salt. If this occurs, the containers should be brought to room temperature. Shake vigorously to assure complete dissolution of any crystals. The speed of dissolution may be increased by heating with circulating warm air. Before use, examine the product to assure that all solids are redissolved and that the container and closure have not been damaged.</paragraph>
                        <paragraph>This product is sensitive to light and must be protected from strong daylight or direct exposure to the sun.</paragraph>
                        <paragraph>As with all contrast media, the containers should be inspected prior to use to ensure that breakage or other damage has not occurred during shipping and handling. All containers should be inspected for closure integrity. Damaged containers should not be used.</paragraph>
                        <paragraph>Manufactured by: <br/>Liebel-Flarsheim Company LLC<br/>Raleigh, NC 27616 </paragraph>
